<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Subject to approval by the appropriate East Georgia College academic department, high school students who participate in an Advanced Placement Program will be awarded appropriate course credit provided a score of three (3) or better is earned on The College Board Advanced Placement Exam (AP). Official test scores should be mailed directly from The College Board to the Office of the Admissions/Registrar for review. Each student will receive confirmation of credit awarded.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.ega.edu/registrar/catalog/Catalog1011.pdf" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

